                  <msItem class="#liturgica" n="1" xml:id="MS_Canon_Liturg_312-item1">
                     <title key="work_11368" type="desc">Consuetudinary (Cistercian)</title>
                     <rubric>Ecclesiastica Officia</rubric>
                     <note>Opens with two sections on the foundation and establishment of the Cistercian order: 'De egressu cisterciensium monachorum de Molismo' (fol. 1) and 'De exordio cistercienssi [sic] cenobii'</note>
                     <note>Main text is the first part of the <title>Liber usuum</title>: an account in 121 chapters of the services, officers and management of a Cistercian monastery</note>
                     <note>Begins: 'In episcopatu Lingonensi' and 'Anno itaque'</note>
                     <note>Chapter 1 begins: 'De Aduentu Domini. capitulum .j. In Aduentu Domini dominica prima Ysaias incipiatur'</note>
                     
